 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">2. Chemical Reactions From First Principles: A Summary of the Theoretical Methodology</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Within the quantum mechanical time independent framework for studies of reaction dynamics, we use the Born-Oppenheimer separation of electronic and nuclear motion and solve the Schrödinger equation for the motion of nuclei</p>
